text: Standish Fletcher Thompson (February 5, 1925 - September 13, 2022) was an American lawyer and Republican politician. He was born in Atlanta, Georgia. He served as a member of the United States House of Representatives from 1967 to 1973 from the 5th Congressional District of Georgia. ==Other websites== * Retrieved on 2008-01-24 Category:1925 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Lawyers from Atlanta Category:United States representatives from Georgia Category:Politicians from Atlanta Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
